{
  "doc_id": "17203",
  "text": "Several preclinical studies have revealed that HDAC inhibitors act as potent radiosensitizers in various cancers, including GBM [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , breast cancer [CITATION_5] , colorectal cancer [CITATION_6] , head and neck cancer [CITATION_7] , non-small-cell lung cancer [CITATION_8] , melanoma [CITATION_9] , and prostate cancer [CITATION_10] . The exact molecular mechanism underlying HDAC inhibitorinduced radiosensitization remains elusive. However, evidence suggests that it partially involves the inhibition of the DNA damage repair response [CITATION_11] . HDAC inhibitors ",
